Running a Windows NT 4.0 VM in Virtualbox
Download Microsoft Windows NT 6 Download
Extract the Windows NT 4 files
Launch Virtualbox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: Windows NT 4
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Microsoft Windows
Version: Windows NT 4
Memory Size: 256 MB
Hard disk: Create a virtual hard disk now

Click Create
On the Create Virtual Hard Disk dialog
Name the virtual disk image Windows NT 4.vdi
File size: 1024 MB
Hard disk file type: VDI
Storage on physical hard disk: Dynamically Allocated

Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select System > Acceleration
Uncheck Enable Nested Paging
Uncheck Enable VT-x/AMD-V
Select Storage
Click on the CD-ROM drive
Select the disc dropdown to the right > Choose a virtual optical disc file...
Browse to the extracted Windows NT 4 files and select the .iso file
Click OK
Make sure the Windows NT VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Press Enter to setup Windows NT
Press Enter to continue
Press C to continue
Page Down until you can press F8 to agree to the Licensing Agreement
Press Enter to accept no changes
Press Enter to install to the Unpartitioned space
Select the 2nd option to partition using the NTFS file system > Press Enter
Press Enter a few more times for good measure
When prompted, remove the CD by selecting Devices > Option Drives > Remove disk from virtual drive
Press Enter to restart the VM
After rebooting a few times you will be prompted to reinsert the CD-ROM
Devices > Option Drives > Choose disk image
Navigate back to the downloaded Windows NT 4 .iso file
Click Open
Click OK inside the VM
Follow the default prompts and then enter a name and organization > Click Next
Give the computer a name > Click Next
Type an administrator password > Re-type to confirm > Click Next
Select No, do not create an emergency repair disk > Click Next
Click Next
Select Wired to the Network > Click Next
Click the Find button and then Next, Next, Next, Continue
Click Yes to use DHCP
Click Next, Next, Finish
Set the date/time and time zone and click close
Wait for the files to copy and Windows 95 to complete initializing
Select a timezone > Click OK
Remove the CD by selecting Devices > Option Drives > Remove
Click the Restart Computer button
Select Input > Keyboard > Insert Ctrl-Alt-Del
Enter the administrator password created earlier and click OK to login
Welcome back to Windows NT 4
Revel in the nostalgia
Optional Steps
Select Devices > Insert Guest Additions CD image...
If VirtualBox Guest Additions doesn't autorun, open My Computer > CD Drive > Double click VBoxWindowsAdditions-x86.exe
Install Guest Additions accepting the defaults
Accept any driver popups from the Guest Additions installer by clicking the Continue Anyway button
After the installation completes select Reboot now > Click Finish
Upon rebooting, you can now full screen the VM and the internal resolution will automatically change to match the window size
Download i12bretro Windows SP.iso Download
Select Devices > Optical Drives > Select disk image...
Navigate to and select i12bretro_Windows_SP.iso
If the VM doesn't autorun, open My Computer > CD Drive
Open the Windows NT folder > Double click Windows NT 4.0 SP6.exe
Follow the dialogs to install Service Pack 6
Click Finish to reboot and complete the SP6 install
